1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,800
Your brain loves evidence that agrees with you—and quietly ignores the rest.

2
00:00:04,800 --> 00:00:09,600
This is called confirmation bias, a cognitive trap we all fall into.

3
00:00:09,600 --> 00:00:12,800
Imagine you’re reading reviews for a new phone.

4
00:00:12,800 --> 00:00:14,400
You love brand X.

5
00:00:14,400 --> 00:00:19,200
You only focus on the glowing reviews and ignore any negative ones.

6
00:00:19,200 --> 00:00:23,600
This skews your perception, making you think the phone is flawless.

7
00:00:23,600 --> 00:00:25,600
Next time, challenge your views.

8
00:00:25,600 --> 00:00:26,800
Seek opposing evidence!
